specJson.description:
In corpus linguistics, part-of-speech tagging (POS tagging or PoS tagging or POST), also called grammatical tagging or word-category disambiguation, is the process of marking up a word in a text (corpus) as corresponding to a particular part of speech, based on both its definition and its context—i.e., its relationship with adjacent and related words in a phrase, sentence, or paragraph. A simplified form of this is commonly taught to school-age children, in the identification of words as nouns, verbs, adjectives, adverbs, etc.

Reference: 
+ <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lexical_analysis#Tokenization>
+ <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Part-of-speech_tagging>

md:
# Tokenizer (Korean) This function tokenizes korean string data into parts of speech(POS). ## Description In corpus linguistics, part-of-speech tagging (POS tagging or PoS tagging or POST), also called grammatical tagging or word-category disambiguation, is the process of marking up a word in a text (corpus) as corresponding to a particular part of speech, based on both its definition and its context—i.e., its relationship with adjacent and related words in a phrase, sentence, or paragraph. A simplified form of this is commonly taught to school-age children, in the identification of words as nouns, verbs, adjectives, adverbs, etc. Reference: + + ## Properties ### VA #### INPUT 1. **table***: (Table) Text data in a Table. #### OUTPUT 1. **table**: (Table) Output Table. It contain input table's columns and tokenized text column. #### PARAMETER 1. **Input Columns***: Columns to select as input. Only String type columns are possible. 2. **Hold Columns**: Result table includes hold columns in input table as well as the result of the operation. If None, all columns are included. 3. **New Column Prefix**: Name of the new column to be added. 4. **Normalization**: Whether to use normalization; the process of canonicalizing tokens so that matches occur despite superficial differences in the character sequences of the tokens. * Available Options: `True`, `False` 5. **Stemming**: Whether to use stemming; the process of reducing inflected words to their word stem, base or root form. * Available Options: `True`, `False` 6. **Extraction**: Extraction of items to return. - Available Options: `Noun`, `Verb`, `Adjective`, `Adverb`, `Determiner`, `Exclamation`, `Josa`, `Eomi`, `PreEomi`, `Conjunction`, `Modifier`, `VerbPrefix`, `Suffix`, `Unknown`, `Korean`, `Foreign`, `Number`, `KoreanParticle`, `Alpha`, `Punctuation`, `Hashtag`, `ScreenName`, `Email`, `URL`, `CashTag`, `Space`, `Others` 7. **Part of Speech Tagging**: Whether to show parts of speech with tokenized words. * Available Options: `True`, `False` ### Python #### USAGE ``` tokenizer_kor(table, input_cols, hold_cols=None, new_col_prefix='tokenized', normalization=True, stemming=True, pos_extraction=None, is_tagged=False) ``` #### INPUT 1. **table***: (Table) Text data in a Table. #### OUTPUT 1. **table**: (Table) Output Table. It contain input table's columns and tokenized text column. #### PARAMETER 1. **input_cols***: Columns to select as input. Only String type columns are possible. * Type: *list[str]* 2. **hold_cols**: Result table includes hold columns in input table as well as the result of the operation. If None, all columns are included. * Type: *list[str]* 3. **new_col_prefix**: Name of the new column to be added. * Type: *str* * Default value: 'tokenized' 4. **normalization**: Whether to use normalization; the process of canonicalizing tokens so that matches occur despite superficial differences in the character sequences of the tokens. * Type: *bool* * Default value: True 5. **stemming**: Whether to use stemming; the process of reducing inflected words to their word stem, base or root form. * Type: *bool* * Default value: True 6. **pos_extraction**: Extraction of items to return. * Type: *list[str]* * Default / Range: Noun ( Noun | Verb | Adjective | Adverb | Determiner | Exclamation | Josa | Eomi | PreEomi | Conjunction | Modifier | VerbPrefix | Suffix | Unknown | Korean | Foreign | Number | KoreanParticle | Alpha | Punctuation | Hashtag | ScreenName | Email | URL | CashTag | Space | Others ) 7. **is_tagged**: Whether to show parts of speech with tokenized words. * Type: *bool* * Default value: False ## Example ### VA **[Sample Model]**
In this tutorial workflow, sample_nsmc data is used as input of Tokenizer(Korean) function. The output of this function is a Table with tokenized text data added to the input Table. The parameter settings used in the function are shown below. ##### ++Parameters++ 1. **Input Columns*** : doc1, doc2 2. **Hold Columns** : None 3. **New Column Prefix** : tokenized 4. **Normalization** : True 5. **Stemming** : True 6. **Extraction** : Select All 7. **Part of Speech Tagging** : False ### Python ``` from brightics.function.textanalytics import tokenizer_kor input_table = inputs[0] result = tokenizer_kor(table=input_table, input_cols=['doc1', 'doc2'], hold_cols=None, new_col_prefix='tokenized', normalization=True, stemming=True, pos_extraction=None, is_tagged=False) output = result['out_table'] ```
In this python script, sample_nsmc data is used as input of tokenizer_kor function. The output of this function is a Table with tokenized text data added to the input Table.
